1))) Where do we find logs for nginx?

ans: 

- name: Get last 10 lines of Nginx error log
  ansible.builtin.command: tail -n 10 /var/log/nginx/error.log
  register: nginx_error_log_tail

- name: Display last 10 lines of Nginx error log
  ansible.builtin.debug:
    var: nginx_error_log_tail.stdout_lines



2)) What is the use of dnf updateinfo list security

ans: “The command dnf updateinfo list security is used to list all security advisories related to installed packages on a Linux system. 
    It’s mainly used for vulnerability management, ensuring only security patches are applied, 
    which is critical in production environments for maintaining system security and compliance.”
